              margin-top: 2px !important; 
            ">President’s Day protests</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/presidents-day-protest-against-trump-and-musk.png" alt="People demonstrated at the Presidents Day protest against President Donald Trump and Elon Musk" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">People demonstrated at the Presidents Day protest against President Donald Trump and Elon Musk. Credits: Tyrone Turner/WAMU/NPR</p>
        </mj-text>

        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5"><strong>Summary: The 50501 movement, which started on Reddit, organized nationwide protests against the Trump administration on President’s Day.</strong></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">On President's Day, cities in all 50 states held “Not My President” protests. The <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-18-02-2025-h1-1-protests-were-organized-by-the-50501-movement?source=website" target="_blank">protests were organized by the 50501 Movement</a>, whose name is derived from its goal: 50 states, 50 protests, and one movement. The protestors chanted, “No King's Day,” and “Not my president,” as they expressed their dismay over the flurry of executive orders aimed at the country’s climate policies, immigration system, and reproductive rights.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">It was created on Reddit and has gained widespread support across social media. Protesters are calling for President Trump's impeachment, Elon Musk's exit from government roles, and the reinstatement of DEI initiatives. They also demand stronger anti-discrimination laws and an investigation into Trump's presidential appointees. Demonstrations from New York to Atlanta to San Francisco marked the largest protests since the second Trump administration.</p>
        </mj-text>
